    {
        "content": "<p>Hi, I was playing through NNG and I reached this weird point while proving anti-symmetry of ≤.</p>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/j_WW3e8j8lbqvPcyNN9abk-3/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/j_WW3e8j8lbqvPcyNN9abk-3/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"923x625\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/j_WW3e8j8lbqvPcyNN9abk-3/image.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div><p>Why was the goal not closed? And what is N as a goal?</p>",
        "id": 536875221,
        "sender_full_name": "Jafar Tanoukhi",
        "timestamp": 1756512687
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>something introduced a metavariable which was not unified</p>",
        "id": 536875261,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756512731
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>do you have a version I can copy into the website</p>",
        "id": 536875266,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756512745
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>not sure if you can directly access the level from here : <a href=\"https://adam.math.hhu.de/#/g/leanprover-community/nng4/world/LessOrEqual/level/6\">https://adam.math.hhu.de/#/g/leanprover-community/nng4/world/LessOrEqual/level/6</a></p>\n<p>also here's the code : </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">cases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hxy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ha</span>\n<span class=\"n\">cases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hyx</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hb</span>\n<span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">ha</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">add_left_eq_self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">zero_add</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hb</span>\n<span class=\"n\">symm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hb</span>\n<span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">add_right_eq_zero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hb</span>\n<span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">hb</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ha</span>\n<span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">add_zero</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ha</span>\n<span class=\"n\">symm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ha</span>\n<span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ha</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 536875316,
        "sender_full_name": "Jafar Tanoukhi",
        "timestamp": 1756512809
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>when you rewrote with <code>add_left_eq_self x</code> you failed to provide the proof that <code>x + y = y</code> and then Lean got couldn't figure out what is <code>y</code> so it put that as a new goal as well</p>",
        "id": 536875398,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756512912
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh I see, by changing it to <code>add_left_eq_self x (a+b)</code> it gave a more \"normal\" result<br>\nbut the goal still did not close after the <code>exact</code> instead i received another goal <code>x + (a + b) = a + b</code></p>\n<p>I assume this has something to do with <code>cases</code> ?</p>",
        "id": 536875681,
        "sender_full_name": "Jafar Tanoukhi",
        "timestamp": 1756513207
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>this has to do with how <code>add_left_eq_self</code> expects you to give it a proof that <code>x + y = y</code></p>",
        "id": 536875703,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756513235
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but you didn't so <code>rw</code> assumed you wanted to do it later and put it into a new goal</p>",
        "id": 536875752,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756513275
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Makes perfect sense thanks!</p>",
        "id": 536876168,
        "sender_full_name": "Jafar Tanoukhi",
        "timestamp": 1756513699
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>by changing it to <code>apply</code> i was able to make it work</p>",
